-b , --batch <number>
Controls actions during file conversion. The <number> may be: 1.
remove silences only; 2. remove silences and smooth privately; 3.
remove silences and smooth publicly.
Privately means with no attempt to reach a public standard,
publicly tries to achieve the selected soundlevel.
Quality is best when privately smoothing,
but uniformity among several files may demand the public option.
